description.narrative:
Associate Professional Officer - OSD


Under supervision of the Director of OSD, direct supervision of a Senior Programme Officer, and guidance from all relevant unit staff members and decentralized offices, the APO will assist the Division in the areas of work detailed below:
-Support the Senior Programme Officer on reviewing the implementation of Host Country Agreements (HCAs) by FAO Member States to ensure  that their commitments with regards to the Organization are fulfilled;
-Support the Programme Officer on drafting, from an OSD perspective, agreements, memorandums of understanding and other texts of a legal nature between FAO and other International Agencies;
-Support the Programme Officer in budgetary and financial matters relating to agreements or projects with FAO Member States and other international agencies;
-Assists the Senior Programme Officer in the preparation of advice, from an OSD perspective and a legal nature, on FAO?s Country Offices relation with their counterpart in the Government;
-Support the informal Team for the establishment of new Partnership and Liaison Offices of FAO throughout the world;
-Assists the Programme Officers in servicing government delegations, including preparation of background materials, summaries of issues and views of delegations, etc.;
-Focal point between OSD and FAO Offices for Spain, Portugal and Japan, and the Community of Portuguese Language Countries (CPLP), reporting directly to the Director of OSD;
-Operational support to the Communications group in content production for the newsletter of the Division, ?Envoy?;
-Production, under request of the Director General's Office, of leaflets on FAO presence at country level, evolution of FAO activities and ongoing projects;
-Support the Communications group on the FAO Representatives' Community Programme;
-Performs other duties as assigned.
